author: NBCNews.com
title: Freak floods in France wash away roads and houses
description: At least eight people are missing after Storm Alex battered the south-east of France, causing what the mayor of Nice said were the worst storms in over a century. The flash floods washed away bridges, leaving villages in the mountainous area cut off.

description: More than 100 people attended the Rose Garden announcement of Amy Coney Barrett as President Trump’s newest Supreme Court nominee. Seven days later, at least eight people who attended have tested positive for Covid-19.
